== Roasted Carrots and Kale ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel, trim, and halve @carrot{6%ounce} lengthwise; cut on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch pieces.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced).

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(thinly sliced).

Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}(chopped into bite-size pieces); chop into bite-size pieces.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), separating whites from greens.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until golden and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Melt 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and garlic; cook, stirring, until golden brown, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; season panko with salt and pepper. Transfer to a #plate{} and set aside. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in same #pan{} over medium heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add kale, 1⁄4 cup water, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until kale is wilted and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired. Transfer to a #large bowl{} and cover with #foil{}. Wash out pan.

== Buffalo Chicken ==

While veggies cook, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @Frank's Seasoning Blend{1/4%ounce}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a second large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

> Simply cook through this step, swapping in chicken for pork.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for kale over medium-low heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add 1⁄4 cup water, @Frank's Hot Sauce{3%unit}, @honey{2%teaspoon}, and @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}. Cook, stirring often, until thickened, ~{1-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until melted and combined. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

When carrots are done roasting, add to bowl with kale; toss to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide chicken and kale jumble between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken; sprinkle kale jumble with as much garlicky panko as you like. Garnish chicken with scallion greens and serve.